## [Support General Global Constraints](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/commit/00988aed70d0c4737014afc4926bed803947a231) introduced some issues

One minor issue was fixed in [this PR](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/pull/6718) however, it is not sufficient for all cases. The following snipped stopped compiling after introduction of support for global constrains - first due to bug which was fixed in mentioned PR however, after fix, it still does not compile and throws an internal error:
```verilog
class RandomValue;
  rand int value;
  constraint small_int_c {
    value < 10;
  }
  task disable_val();
    value.rand_mode(0);
  endtask
endclass

class Base;
  rand RandomValue v = new;
endclass

class Foo extends Base;
endclass

module t;
  initial begin
    Foo d = new;
    Base b = d;
    b.v.disable_val();
    b.v.value = 11;
    if (bit'(b.randomize())) $stop;
    if (b.v.value != 11) $stop;
    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

